{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-06-25T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Zoom in on the small interaction that helps keep landscapes alive: a butterfly on a yellow flower, pausing for nectar. While it feeds, pollen dusts its body and hitches a ride to the next bloom—one of the quiet ways flowering plants reproduce. Pollinators are not only bees. Butterflies, birds, bats, beetles and many other animals help move pollen, supporting wild plants and many of the fruits and vegetables people eat.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BFPollin_ROW9877719219_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BFPollin_ROW9877719219_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Butterfly pollinating on yellow flower","Copyright":"© lzh/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260624_BFPollin\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Butterfly&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260624_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260624_BFPollin"},"Ssd":"20260624","Name":"BFPollin","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9877719219","FullDateString":"Jun 24, jjjj"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Mount Fuji, Japan's highest mountain, rises to 3,776 metres on Honshu Island, about 97 kilometres southwest of Tokyo. Its near-perfect cone is a volcano—dormant since its last eruption in December 1707 yet still classed as active. That last major event is known as the Hōei eruption. It blasted ash and other tephra across eastern Japan, reaching Edo (today's Tokyo). Beyond geology, Fuji has long been treated as a sacred landscape and a destination for pilgrimage climbs, reflecting how nature, religion and daily life overlap in Japan. That enduring cultural appeal is one reason it was designated a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2013 as 'a sacred place and source of artistic inspiration.' Fuji is famously visible from far away on clear days but never guaranteed—clouds can hide it in minutes. Whether you hike it or just catch a glimpse from a train window, it still feels like Japan's signature on the horizon.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Fujisan_ROW9816660784_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Fujisan_ROW9816660784_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Mount Fuji on Honshu Island, Japan","Copyright":"© phutthiseth thongtae/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260623_Fujisan\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Mount+Fuji&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260623_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260623_Fujisan"},"Ssd":"20260623","Name":"Fujisan","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9816660784","FullDateString":"Jun 23, jjjj"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Rainforests aren't just dots on the map. They thrive across the tropics and beyond, yet cover only about 6% of Earth's surface. Quinault, in Olympic National Park in Washington state, is a primeval temperate rainforest on the Olympic Peninsula, where Pacific moisture creates ideal conditions for dense growth. Rain and drifting fog keep the forest thriving, turning branches, trunks and even fallen logs into living surfaces.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.QuinaultFerns_ROW9752257605_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.QuinaultFerns_ROW9752257605_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Quinault rainforest, Olympic National Park, Washington state, United States","Copyright":"© Chris Moore/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260622_QuinaultFerns\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Rainforest+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260622_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260622_QuinaultFerns"},"Ssd":"20260622","Name":"QuinaultFerns","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9752257605","FullDateString":"Jun 22, jjjj"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Above the Tarn Valley, the Millau Viaduct seems to brush the sky. At 343 metres, its highest pylons rise taller than the Eiffel Tower. At dawn, light mist often drifts between the hills of the Larzac plateau and Aveyron, wrapping steel and concrete in an almost unreal softness. From some viewpoints, the bridge can appear to float above the clouds rather than standing upon them.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MillauViaductFrance_ROW0201721820_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MillauViaductFrance_ROW0201721820_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Millau Viaduct, France","Copyright":"© Sergi Reboredo/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260621_MillauViaductFrance\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Millau+Viaduct&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260621_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260621_MillauViaductFrance"},"Ssd":"20260621","Name":"MillauViaductFrance","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0201721820","FullDateString":"Jun 21, jjjj"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"A sculpted arch of ice rises from the Southern Ocean along the Antarctic Peninsula, one of the fastest-warming regions on Earth. This formation began as compacted snow that turned into glacial ice over thousands of years. Eventually, part of a glacier or floating ice shelf fractured and broke free—a process known as calving—creating a drifting iceberg.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ArchedIceberg_ROW4666187976_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ArchedIceberg_ROW4666187976_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Arched iceberg floating off the western Antarctic Peninsula, Southern Ocean","Copyright":"© Steven Kazlowski/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260620_ArchedIceberg\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Iceberg&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260620_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260620_ArchedIceberg"},"Ssd":"20260620","Name":"ArchedIceberg","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4666187976","FullDateString":"Jun 20, jjjj"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Perched at the far edge of Piazza Bovio in Piombino, Tuscany, Italy, is the Piombino Lighthouse. Locally, it is known as 'Faro di Piombino' or 'La Rocchetta Lighthouse.' It overlooks the point where the Tuscan coast faces the island of Elba.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.IsolaElba_ROW4135146629_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.IsolaElba_ROW4135146629_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"La Rocchetta Lighthouse, Piombino, Tuscany, Italy","Copyright":"© StevanZZ/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260619_IsolaElba\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=La+Rocchetta+Lighthouse&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260619_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260619_IsolaElba"},"Ssd":"20260619","Name":"IsolaElba","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4135146629","FullDateString":"Jun 19, jjjj"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Set high above Cusco in Peru, Sacsayhuamán reveals the ambition of the Inca Empire in stone. Built in the 15th century, this vast complex once formed part of the sacred capital of the Incas. From above, the layout becomes clear: terraces, open plazas and the remains of towers forming a carefully planned citadel. The largest walls, built from enormous blocks, still stand strong today. Some stones rise more than 8.2 metres tall and were fitted together so precisely—without mortar—that the structure has endured centuries of earthquakes.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Saqsaywaman_ROW9340385062_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Saqsaywaman_ROW9340385062_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Aerial view of the ruins of Sacsayhuamán, Cusco, Peru","Copyright":"© Creative-Family/Getty Images Plus","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260618_Saqsaywaman\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Sacsayhuaman+Cusco+Peru&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260618_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260618_Saqsaywaman"},"Ssd":"20260618","Name":"Saqsaywaman","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9340385062","FullDateString":"Jun 18, jjjj"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today's image takes us to Dungeon Provincial Park on the rugged coast of Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada, where nature tells a much older story. Atlantic waves carved a sea cave with two openings, gradually widening it until the roof gave way. What remains is a striking collapsed formation known as a 'gloup,' surrounded by steep cliffs and crashing surf.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.DungeonPark_ROW7201602273_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.DungeonPark_ROW7201602273_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Dungeon Provincial Park, Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada","Copyright":"© Kaitlyn McLachlan/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260701_DungeonPark\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Dungeon+Provincial+Park+Canada&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260701_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260701_DungeonPark"},"Ssd":"20260701","Name":"DungeonPark","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7201602273","FullDateString":"Jul 1, jjjj"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As the sun sinks low in the Masai Mara National Reserve, the silhouettes of Masai giraffes rise against a blazing sky and open plains. Another day comes to an end in the reserve, which stretches across about 1,500 square kilometres in southwestern Kenya, bordering Tanzania's Serengeti National Park. It is a vast expanse, one of the world's greatest wildlife arenas. Rolling grasslands, scattered acacia trees and the life-giving Mara River set the stage for unforgettable encounters.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiGiraffe_ROW6806132366_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiGiraffe_ROW6806132366_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Giraffes at sunset in the Masai Mara National Reserve, Kenya","Copyright":"© danm/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260630_MasaiGiraffe\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Masai+Mara+National+Reserve&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260630_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260630_MasaiGiraffe"},"Ssd":"20260630","Name":"MasaiGiraffe","Market":"ROW","Hash":"6806132366","FullDateString":"Jun 30, jjjj"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Beyond its postcard views, Bora Bora has a deeper story to tell. Its lagoon reflects how tropical islands evolve over time. Surrounded by shades of turquoise, this island in French Polynesia is home to one of the South Pacific's most celebrated lagoons, where coral reefs, volcanic peaks and ocean life exist side by side.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BoraBoraLagoon_ROW6505126632_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BoraBoraLagoon_ROW6505126632_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Bora Bora and its lagoon, South Pacific, French Polynesia","Copyright":"© Frederick Millett/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260629_BoraBoraLagoon\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bora+Bora&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260629_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260629_BoraBoraLagoon"},"Ssd":"20260629","Name":"BoraBoraLagoon","Market":"ROW","Hash":"6505126632","FullDateString":"Jun 29, jjjj"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"'Stick around' takes on a new meaning in the Sonoran Desert, where the saguaro cactus has mastered survival. With trunks and arms raised in all directions, this giant has become the American Southwest's mascot.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SaguaroSun_ROW6246109819_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SaguaroSun_ROW6246109819_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Saguaro cacti near Windgate Pass, McDowell Range, Arizona, United States","Copyright":"© Eric Mischke/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260628_SaguaroSun\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Saguaro+cactus&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260628_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260628_SaguaroSun"},"Ssd":"20260628","Name":"SaguaroSun","Market":"ROW","Hash":"6246109819","FullDateString":"Jun 28, jjjj"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At Boneyard Beach within Hunting Island State Park, South Carolina, United States, the first thing you notice is the trees. Then comes the question: why are bleached trunks and exposed roots scattered across the sand like a scene paused midway through collapse? Since the 1980s, Hunting Island has experienced major beach erosion, with some of the highest rates along the US East Coast—reaching up to 9 metres per year in certain areas.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BoneyardBeach_ROW5980184079_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BoneyardBeach_ROW5980184079_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Driftwood on Boneyard Beach, Hunting Island, South Carolina, USA","Copyright":"© Frances/Adobe Stock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260627_BoneyardBeach\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Hunting+Island&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260627_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260627_BoneyardBeach"},"Ssd":"20260627","Name":"BoneyardBeach","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5980184079","FullDateString":"Jun 27, jjjj"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What does a parliament, a clock tower and a giant wheel have in common? They all stand beside the River Thames as if London had carefully staged its icons for dramatic effect.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ThamesSummer_ROW5725205310_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ThamesSummer_ROW5725205310_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"The River Thames, London, England","Copyright":"© Daniel Lange/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260626_ThamesSummer\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=River+Thames&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260626_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260626_ThamesSummer"},"Ssd":"20260626","Name":"ThamesSummer","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5725205310","FullDateString":"Jun 26, jjjj"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Few squares in Belgium wear history as well as the Grand Place. The surrounding buildings, seen here, began as guild houses, each funded by a specific trade. Brewers, bakers, merchants and craftsmen treated architecture as language, translating work, status and rivalry into stone through reliefs, coats of arms and generous gold leaf. Styles meet without caution. Gothic verticals rise beside Baroque curves, while the Town Hall, older than its neighbours and unapologetically asymmetrical, holds the composition together.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GrandPlace_ROW9942052634_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GrandPlace_ROW9942052634_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Buildings on Grand-Place Square in Brussels, Belgium","Copyright":"© Vladislav Zolotov/Getty Images Plus","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260625_GrandPlace\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Grand+Place+Brussels&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260625_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260625_GrandPlace"},"Ssd":"20260625","Name":"GrandPlace","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9942052634","FullDateString":"Jun 25, jjjj"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Beeld van die dag","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Kom meer te wete","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Skenk nou","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Kitsf